HEADWORD: Hemimetabolic
<hw>Hem`i*met`a*bol"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having an incomplete metamorphosis, the larvae
differing from the adults chiefly in laking wings, as in the
grasshoppers and cockroaches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hemimorphic</ent>⟦br⟧
